                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="major" script="naskh">
                                <desc>Script: Naskh. Scribes: Most of the first part (<locus
                                        from="1b" to="295b">ff. 1b-295b</locus> and <locus
                                        from="305a" to="369b">305a-369b</locus>) seem to be in the
                                    same hand, which (judging by a note in the first half) is that
                                    of <persName key="" role="scr">
                                        <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x">Şāhī bin Muḥammed
                                            Tüsterī</persName>
                                        <persName xml:lang="ota">شاهی بن محمد تستری</persName>
                                    </persName>. A second, anonymous hand is responsible for the
                                    remainder of the first part (<locus from="296a" to="303b">ff.
                                        296a-303b</locus>), written on lighter-coloured paper,
                                    suggesting perhaps a post-factum replacement for missing pages.
                                    A third, again anonymous hand is responsible for three separate
                                    sections of the second part (<locus from="371a" to="378b">ff.
                                        371a-378b</locus>, <locus from="380a" to="498b">ff.
                                        380a-498b</locus>, and <locus from="507a" to="521b">ff.
                                        507a-521b</locus>), whereas a fourth and final anonymous
                                    hand is evident in the remaining sections of the second part
                                        (<locus from="370b" to="370b">ff. 370b</locus>, <locus
                                        from="379a" to="379b">379a-b</locus>, and <locus from="499a"
                                        to="506b">499a-506b</locus>). Remarkably, despite
                                    considerable differences in line height between some of these
                                    hands, a consistent number of lines per page has been maintained
                                    throughout by varying the height and width of the column.</desc>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote>Illuminated frontispieces for each part on <locus from="1b"
                                    to="1b">f. 1b</locus> and <locus from="370b" to="370b">f.
                                    370b</locus>.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <p>Red binding with gold-painted stamped decoration.</p>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>The first part is dated to <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                when="1601-12">early Receb 1010</origDate>
                            <origDate calendar="#Gregorian" when="1609-10-09">late December
                                1601</origDate>. Given that a statement of ownership in the second
                            part (370a) dates to <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notAfter="1726"
                                >1138</origDate>
                            <origDate calendar="#Gregorian" notAfter="1726">1725/6</origDate>, it is
                            highly likely that that part was completed before then. </origin>
                        <provenance>According to a note on <locus from="1a" to="1a">f. 1a</locus>,
                            either the whole work or the first part (<locus from="1b" to="295b">ff.
                                1b-295b</locus>) entered the collection of one <persName>حسن بن حسین
                                </persName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1697">25
                                Muḥarrem 1109</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1697">13
                                August 1697</date>.</provenance>
                        <provenance>According to a note on <locus from="1a" to="1a">f. 1a</locus>,
                            either the whole work or the first part (<locus from="1b" to="295b">ff.
                                1b-295b</locus>) entered the collection of vālide ketḫüdāsı
                                <persName>محمد صادق</persName> in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                cert="medium" when="1713">(11)25</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian"
                                cert="medium" when="1713">(17)13</date>.</provenance>
                        <provenance>According to a note on <locus from="370b" to="370b">f.
                                370b</locus>, the second part of the work (<locus from="370b"
                                to="521b">ff. ff. 370b-521b</locus>) entered the collection of one
                                <persName>الحاج محمد راقم</persName> in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                when="1726">1139</date>/<date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1726"
                                >1726</date>.</provenance>
                        <provenance>The collections of <persName key="person_76658435" role="fmo"
                                >George Sale, d. <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1736"
                                >1736</date></persName>.</provenance>
                        <provenance>The collections of <persName key="person_76658435" role="fmo"
                                >George Sale, d. <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1736"
                                >1736</date></persName>.</provenance>
                        <acquisition>Acquired by the Bodleian Library in <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                                when="1872">1826</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
